Template: mico-marmotta/title
Type: title
Description: MICO Marmotta Configuration


Template: mico-marmotta/database-name
Type: string
Default: marmotta
Description: Name of PostgreSQL database to use for Marmotta:
 Configure the name of the database to use for Marmotta. In case the database does not exist, the setup script allows
 to automatically create it (select "Yes" in the respective question). Marmotta will automatically create its tables
 when starting up.

Template: mico-marmotta/database-user
Type: string
Default: marmotta
Description: Name of PostgreSQL user to use for Marmotta:
 Configure the database user used by Marmotta to access the PostgreSQL database. In case the user does not exist,
 the setup script allows to automatically create it (select "Yes" in the respective question).

Template: mico-marmotta/database-password
Type: password
Default: ${dbpass}
Description: Name of PostgreSQL user to use for Marmotta:
 Configure the database password used by Marmotta to access the PostgreSQL database. In case the user does not exist,
 the setup script allows to automatically create it (select "Yes" in the respective question).


Template: mico-marmotta/create-database
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Create Marmotta database and user?
 If you select "Yes" here, the setup script will automatically create the PostgreSQL database and user configured in
 the previous steps. If you select "No", the setup script will only update the Marmotta configuration with the values
 you provided; in this case you need to make sure the database exists and is accessible.
